                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The problem with giving advice on playing a necro is that every situation demands that the necro plays a different role and uses different spells. You need to adapt to each situation.<br /><br />All the same here's a few random thoughts and tips on what to do and not to do at 54th:<br /><br />Don't use the 53 rogue pet unless you are constantly fear kiting - use the 49 pet instead (it is much sturdier)<br /><br />Do keep your pet buffed (you will be only be able to cast Intensify Death until 55th but it makes a big difference)<br /><br />Watch out for lich death! You should almost always be in lich form for mana regen but you have to watch your HPs <br /><br />Do use Bond of Death and Deflux to keep your HPs topped up (and the mob hurting) even when liched and or healing others with Shadow Compact<br /><br />Don't use cascading darkness (it takes too long to cast) - just use Dooming Darkness (29th) instead (I still use Doom a lot even in place of Devouring Darkness at level 62)<br /><br />Use paralysing earth for outdoor fights where you want a long lasting root - only consider using Enstill if you are LOM or don't need too root for long. <br /><br />Splurt is your most mana efficient spell but it needs to run its full course to be effective - so cast it early. Combine with Ignite Blood (also mana efficient) for non root breaking Dotting. Only use EBolt if you want a quick kill and be ready for massive aggro if you do!<br /><br />Shackle of spirit is very nice (39th) to use on undead to "pet tank" using Bond of Death then Shadowbond to heal your pet.<br /><br />Insidious Retrogression is nice for fast fights where you want the mob snared for a short time.<br /><br />Have a look at the guide section of this site and check out the necro damage chart for full spell details.<br /><br />Always have FD and Harmshield memed for sticky situations. Cast FD first and if that fails or you can't get it off cast HS, run for it then FD again.<br /><br />Keep control of your pet with hotkeys to /pet back off /pet sit down (they regen faster sitting) /pet follow me /pet attack /pet get lost etc etc. And use Summon Companion to get your pet back if it wanders or invis to kill it when it does this and agrros stuff (best to use items for this - CoS and Shiverback(?) Belt<br /><br />If you need to lose your pet to head off somewhere invis then use reclaim energy before you invis (you may as well get some mana back)<br /><br />Good luck - don't play like a monkey or other necros will spit on you because a necro played badly REALLY sucks just as much as a necro played well rocks.<br /><br />Falrinth<br />62 Warlock<br />Cazic Thule</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
