                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Charming is one of the best xp methods in the game.  Once you get it down you can do in AA in under 4 hours in ME.  However, it's one of the more advanced and possibly dangerous (get an inconvient root break and charm at the same time...bad).  <br /><br />You're gonna want to stay away from popular zones.  These probably include anywhere in PoP and popular old world grind spots.  No experience personally, but I bet they are prime PK ground if another team owns the zone.  Neriak ogres/trolls are probably one of these...not sure if it's controlled by evil or not (I assume a necro is evil).  <br /><br />Probably the most common and generally best way to kill a random blue mob is fear kite.  Pull with darkness, Invoke Fear, a DoT and BoD while keeping (hasted) pet on it and Lich up all  the time.  The L53 pet Minion of Shadows is a rogue...therefore has minimal HP and tanking ability, but has great damage when fearkiting or agrokiting.  The 49 pet is a warrior and has a lot more HP but substantially less damage output.  He's still better if you plan to pet-tank (use Shadowbond to heal your pet and BoD to get your HP back, just let your buffed pet rip it a new one.  You can lay on a DoT or two and darkness) for his HP and the fact that the rogue needs back exposure to do it's damage.  Slow any undead mobs you fight with Shackle of Spirit.<br /><br />Travel...PoP ports should be fine I think.  Most important buff is probably SoW when you have it I guess.  HP and resists are really important too I imagine.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
