                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> for exp you can go to Twilight...across from the katta zone is an island with 2 docks.  3 mobs per dock, and the katta dock has 2 more.  that is 8 single pullable mobs.<br /><br />i did them long before the pet changes so i used root/DoT...2 dooming, 1 splurt, and 1 ignite killed them.  max hit was around 98.  <br />------<br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Do keep your pet buffed (you will be only be able to cast Intensify Death until 55th but it makes a big difference)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />i think you mean augment which is lvl 39 (it is also the right click effect off of velious quest pants).<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Do use Bond of Death and Deflux to keep your HPs topped up <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />don't worry too much about being 'topped up'.  you shouldn't be getting hit so 100% HP isn't that important, and keeping it can just be a waiste of mana.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Don't use cascading darkness (it takes too long to cast) - just use Dooming Darkness (29th) instead (I still use Doom a lot even in place of Devouring Darkness at level 62)<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />this is more of a personal preference.  when fear kiting dooming is normally better.  but if you are root/DoTing the damage on cascading isn't that bad.<br />-----<br /><br />ok i'm done adding to his post, hehe.  check out the <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=10811">PLEASE READ::Necromancer Index::PLEASE READ</a> at the top of this page.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/"><br />Abillister "Monkey" Abu - Inverse Logic<br /><img src="http://www.finitesite.com/yenmabek/10372061.jpg" align=left></a><br /><img src="http://www.gsarchives.com/pc/sprites/monkeyisland2/Monkey_Dance.gif" width=103 height=99 align=center></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
