                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I group 98 pct of the time.<br /><br />If you have at least 2 tanks, Degeneration rocks.  Add's 30 sta/str for 6 minutes to whole group.  At 61 I still use this regularly.<br /><br />Dots other then EB aren't really mana efficient in groups, I'll nuke more.  If pulling undead mobs, you can slow them for group so ya can do without chanter/shaman.<br /><br />If you don't have a chanter, keep Screaming Terror memmed for those adds.  Pretty much takes you out of the fight but you can still send pet in and deflux between casts (or ToM if you get to 61).<br /><br />If you have a SK in group, don't worry about Succession of Shadows and Crippling Claudication.  They have group taps for AC/ATK and Degeneration will complement them very well.<br /><br />I personally don't cast those even if we don't have a SK, I don't see the manausage as benefitting the group that much.<br /><br />I rarely buff my pet with the 55 buff, it rocks but I'm lazy =P.  I'll cast pants on pet or let the chanter snakestick them.  I have Rune of Death but not 62 yet, I will most likely buff pet when I get that level (and finally get LoZ).<br /><br />I find soloing boring as hell, I play this game to hang out with friends and I find grouping much funner, even if the pulls suck from overcamping.<br /><br />No advice on the zek stuff, I'm a bluebie and proud of it.<br /><br />Lykos D'Lich<br />Krieger<br />Tunare</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
